liblzmadec
--------------------------------------
liblzmadec0 and liblzmadec-devel provide a library suitable
for decompressing files in the .lzma (that is, 'LZMA-Alone'
format.  It will soon be replaced by liblzma from the XZ Utils
package (distributed on cygwin as 'xz'); the new library 
supports both compression and decompression. However, 
liblzmadec is still in wide use, and this package allows
dependent projects to continue without change until they
desire to upgrade.

Utility programs formerly contained in the cygwin 'lzma'
package are now shipped in the cygwin 'xz' package. When
built by this cygport, those files are placed in a dummy
"package" named 'leftovers'.

